<page>
    <topic>ARRAY.RESIZE Function</topic>
    <description>Resize an array, keeping its components intact.</description>  
    <syntax>V &lt;ARRAY&gt;.resize(size as N [,dimension as N])</syntax>
    <arguments>
        <argument>
            <name>size</name>
            <type>N</type>
            <description>The new number of elements in the array.</description>
        </argument>
        <argument optional="true">
            <name>dimension</name>
            <type>N</type>
            <description>Default value is 1. The dimension of the array to resize.</description>
        </argument>
    </arguments>
    <discussion>The &lt;ARRAY&gt;.RESIZE() method increases the size of an array, without losing any of the existing data, as the [REDIM] command would.</discussion>
    <example><![CDATA[dim fruit[3,2] as C
fruit[1,1] = "Apple"
fruit[2,1] = "Banana"
fruit[3,1] = "Cherry"
fruit.resize(4,1)

? fruit
= [1,1] = "Apple"
[1,2] = ""
[2,1] = "Banana"
[2,2] = ""
[3,1] = "Cherry"
[3,2] = ""
[4,1] = ""
[4,2] = ""

fruit.resize(3,2)

? fruit
= [1,1] = "Apple"
[1,2] = ""
[1,3] = ""
[2,1] = "Banana"
[2,2] = ""
[2,3] = ""
[3,1] = "Cherry"
[3,2] = ""
[3,3] = ""
[4,1] = ""
[4,2] = ""
[4,3] = ""]]></example>
